      • getFlowId

        protected java.lang.String getFlowId(org.springframework.core.io.Resource flowResource)
        Obtains the flow id from the flow resource. By default, the flow id becomes the portion of the path between the basePath and the filename. If no directory structure is available then the filename without the extension is used. Subclasses may override.

        For example, '${basePath}/booking.xml' becomes 'booking' and '${basePath}/hotels/booking/booking.xml' becomes 'hotels/booking'

        Parameters:
        flowResource - the flow resource
        Returns:
        the flow id
